```

The first part of the conjunction is `i ∈ fin_range n`. Since `fin_range n` is `List.replicate n 0`, `i ∈ fin_range n` means `i ∈ List.replicate n 0`. The definition of `List.mem_replicate` is `∃ k, k < n ∧ i = 0`. But `i` is `Fin n`, so `i` is already less than `n`. The definition of `Fin.is_lt` is `i.1 < n`. So `i ∈ fin_range n` is true by `Fin.is_lt i`.

The second part of the conjunction is `f i = f i`, which is trivially true by `rfl`.

The third part is `(f i)[↑j] ∈ f i`. This is true by `List.get_mem`. The definition of `List.get_mem` is `List.get_mem (l : List α) (i : Fin l.length) : l.get i ∈ l`.

So we can complete the proof:
```tactics
constructor
· -- Show f i = f i
  rfl
