8. This requires showing `i.1 < n` (for the `Fin n` type) and that `i` is in the range of indices produced by `mapFinIdx`.
9. Since `i : Fin n`, by definition `i.1 < n` is true. The structure of `fin_range` ensures that all indices `a` in `fin_range n` satisfy `a.1 < n`.
10. Therefore, `i ∈ fin_range n` is true.

So the first part of the conjunction is true with `a = i`.

