The membership condition `rule ∈ RelInt.liftFinf n f` means `rule` is an element of the flattened list. This is equivalent to saying there exists some `k` such that `f k = rule` or `rule` is nested within the lists produced by `f`.

But we have `rule = (f i).get j`, which means `rule` is an element of the list `f i`. Since `f i` is one of the lists being concatenated by `fin_range n |>.map f |>.flatten`, `rule` is indeed in the final flattened list.

